      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T00:21:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e \u003e \"modbus\" is not a type.  That device might have multiple interfaces, \n\u003e \n\u003e Modbus isn\u0027t a device type -- it\u0027s used here as an interface qualifier to indicate which interface of the device this config refers to, since a device can have multiple interfaces.\n\nIf the device has multiple interfaces, that\u0027s fine, they would all go under the one stanza.  That\u0027s the important thing here, the IMPLEMENTATION needs to own correctly connecting to that device, not the (sometimes arbitrary) config.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e \n\u003e \u003e and certainly doesn\u0027t share all these properties in common.  \n\u003e \n\u003e All Modbus devices share these connection properties (BaudRate, DataParity, Address, etc.) -- the BMC needs them to configure the serial port before communicating with any Modbus device.\n\nNo, they don\u0027t share everything, that\u0027s the point.  Even if they did, and I invented a device next week that does modbus at 1gbps, that value isn\u0027t valid for any of these.  Even if they support multple, they support some RANGE that\u0027s specific to the device.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e \u003e A PanasonicBJBPM102A0001PMM has a known baud rate (or set of baud rates). It shouldn\u0027t be reading from a common type with all those properties.  We should only allow the properties that differs FOR THAT DEVICE.\n\u003e \n\u003e The BaudRate is known by device but when BMC has to talk to the device it needs to set the same BaudRate on the serial link.\n\nRight, which it should be looking up in the backend.  These config files are meant to only include the DIFFERENCES between systems;  Similarities need to go in code, otherwise we duplicate parameters everywhere.\n\n\u003e Also, on same port we can have multiple different types of devices daisy chained which run at different BaudRates/Parity etc, so this needs to be configured before talking to a device.\n\nUnderstood that.  Address seems completely reasonable to have in this file.  The rest doesn\u0027t.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e \u003e We should only allow the properties that differs FOR THAT DEVICE.\n\u003e \n\u003e Yes, these are all the properties which differ FOR THAT DEVICE.\n\nYou said yourself that baud rate at a minimum doesn\u0027t.  I\u0027m pretty sure whether or not a device supports parity is also not per device.  SensorRegisters is another good example of us adding stuff into this config that shouldn\u0027t be there.  Put that in code.",
      "parentUuid": "a748b394_84336ab3",
      "revId": "e5bdf248b1acfda6f3ed93e2c3732a0a151c68dd",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
